<subsection xml:id="subsec-tree_diagram">
    <title>Tree Diagram</title>
        <p>
            A tree diagram is a visual tool used to show all possible outcomes of two or more events,
            especially when calculating probabilities of combined or successive events.
        </p>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Construct a tree diagram for tossing a coin twice.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Label the branches with:
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        First toss: H or T  each with <m> \frac{1}{2} </m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        Second toss: H or T again each with <m> \frac{1}{2} </m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the probability of each e.g(P(HH), P(HT))
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
     
        </activity>
        <p>  
            <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            It helps organize outcomes in branches and is particularly useful for independent events.
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A bag has 2 red and 1 green marble. A marble is drawn, replaced, 
                    then another is drawn. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Draw a tree diagram and find the probability of getting
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Two red marbles
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                One red and one green (in any order)
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Total marbles <m>= 3</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <m> \textbf{P(Red)} = \frac{2}{3} </m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <m>\textbf{P(Green)} =  \frac{1}{3}</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Tree Diagram where R = P(Red) and G = P(Green)
                            </p>
                            <image width="60%">
                            <latex-image label="tree-diagram-green">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}[
                                    grow=right,
                                    sibling distance=1.1cm,
                                    level distance=0.8cm,
                                    edge from parent/.style={draw,thick},
                                    scale=2.4,
                                    every node/.style={font=\footnotesize, inner sep=2pt}
                                    ]

                                    \node[circle, draw, thick] (Start) {}
                                    child { node[circle, draw] (R) {R}
                                        child { node[circle, draw, yshift=0.8cm] (RG_R) {RG}
                                            edge from parent node[below, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{1}{3}$}
                                        }
                                        child { node[circle, draw, yshift=-0.8cm] (RR_R) {RR}
                                            edge from parent node[above, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{2}{3}$}
                                        }
                                        edge from parent node[below, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{2}{3}$}
                                    }
                                    child { node[circle, draw] (G) {G}
                                        child { node[circle, draw, yshift=0.8cm] (GG_G) {GG}
                                            edge from parent node[below, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{1}{3}$}
                                        }
                                        child { node[circle, draw, yshift=-0.8cm] (GR_G) {GR}
                                            edge from parent node[above, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{2}{3}$}
                                        }
                                        edge from parent node[above, midway, font=\scriptsize] {$\frac{1}{3}$}
                                    };
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>                  
                            </image>                     
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                P(Red and Red)
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> = \frac{2}{3} × \frac{2}{3} = \frac{4}{9} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                (Red then Green)
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> = \frac{2}{3} × \frac{1}{3} = \frac{2}{9} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                P(Green then Red)
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> = \frac{1}{3} × \frac{2}{3} = \frac{2}{9} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Total
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> = \frac{2}{9} + \frac{2}{9} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
     
</subsection>